"{\"uid\": \"ncregister.com-cna-catholic-bishops-around-the-world-demand-ioc-formal-apology-for-blasphemous-olympic-opening\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"EWTN News, Inc. is the world's largest Catholic news organization, comprised of television, radio, print and digital media outlets, dedicated to reporting the truth in light of the Gospel and the Catholic Church.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 244, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 4, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/EWTN\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"EWTN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/EWTN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/EWTN\"}, {\"begin\": 39, \"end\": 47, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1841076763910413e-20, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 197, \"end\": 203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gospel\", \"score\": 0.9999341069970641, \"rank\": 5.59408511995289e-05, \"text\": \"Gospel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gospel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gospel\"}, {\"begin\": 228, \"end\": 243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.1016934536434e-21, \"text\": \"Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Inc.\", \"from\": 11, \"to\": 15}, {\"ngram\": \"television\", \"from\": 80, \"to\": 90}, {\"ngram\": \"radio\", \"from\": 92, \"to\": 97}, {\"ngram\": \"print\", \"from\": 99, \"to\": 104}, {\"ngram\": \"digital media outlets\", \"from\": 109, \"to\": 130}, {\"ngram\": \"the truth\", \"from\": 155, \"to\": 164}, {\"ngram\": \"light\", \"from\": 168, \"to\": 173}, {\"ngram\": \"the Gospel\", \"from\": 177, \"to\": 187}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Subscribe for just$49.95$32.50!\", \"from\": 246, \"to\": 277, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"just$49.95$32.50\", \"from\": 260, \"to\": 276}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The letter was signed by three cardinals and 24 bishops as of Friday, Aug. 2.\", \"from\": 279, \"to\": 356, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The letter\", \"from\": 279, \"to\": 289}, {\"ngram\": \"three cardinals\", \"from\": 304, \"to\": 319}, {\"ngram\": \"24 bishops\", \"from\": 324, \"to\": 334}, {\"ngram\": \"Friday\", \"from\": 341, \"to\": 347}, {\"ngram\": \"Aug.\", \"from\": 349, \"to\": 353}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a strongly worded open letter, Catholic cardinals and bishops from around the world are calling on the International Olympic Committee (IOC) to \\\"repudiate\\\" and \\\"apologize\\\" for the \\\"intentionally hateful mockery\\\"of the Last Supperduring the opening ceremony of the Paris 2024 Olympics.\", \"from\": 358, \"to\": 645, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 392, \"end\": 400, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1841076763910413e-20, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 464, \"end\": 501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a strongly worded open letter\", \"from\": 361, \"to\": 390}, {\"ngram\": \"bishops\", \"from\": 415, \"to\": 422}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 435, \"to\": 444}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"intentionally hateful mockery\\\"of\", \"from\": 537, \"to\": 574}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supperduring\", \"from\": 575, \"to\": 596}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 597, \"to\": 617}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris 2024 Olympics\", \"from\": 621, \"to\": 644}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition, \\\"the undersigned commit to a day of prayer and fasting in reparation for this blasphemy.\\\"\", \"from\": 647, \"to\": 749, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"addition\", \"from\": 650, \"to\": 658}, {\"ngram\": \"a day\", \"from\": 687, \"to\": 692}, {\"ngram\": \"prayer\", \"from\": 696, \"to\": 702}, {\"ngram\": \"reparation\", \"from\": 718, \"to\": 728}, {\"ngram\": \"this blasphemy\", \"from\": 733, \"to\": 747}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The letter was signed by three cardinals and 24 bishops as of Friday, Aug. 2, and states: \\\"With shock, the world watched as the Summer Olympics in Paris opened with a grotesque and blasphemous depiction of the Last Supper.\\\"\", \"from\": 751, \"to\": 974, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 898, \"end\": 903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999430383485, \"rank\": 5.6961509846668786e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The letter\", \"from\": 751, \"to\": 761}, {\"ngram\": \"three cardinals\", \"from\": 776, \"to\": 791}, {\"ngram\": \"24 bishops\", \"from\": 796, \"to\": 806}, {\"ngram\": \"Friday\", \"from\": 813, \"to\": 819}, {\"ngram\": \"Aug.\", \"from\": 821, \"to\": 825}, {\"ngram\": \"shock\", \"from\": 847, \"to\": 852}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 854, \"to\": 863}, {\"ngram\": \"the Summer Olympics\", \"from\": 875, \"to\": 894}, {\"ngram\": \"a grotesque and blasphemous depiction\", \"from\": 916, \"to\": 953}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 957, \"to\": 972}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It is hard to understand how the faith of over 2 billion people can be so casually and intentionally blasphemed,\\\" say the prelates, who include Cardinal Raymond Leo Burke; Cardinal Wilfrid Fox Napier, OFM; and Cardinal Berhaneyesus Demerew Souraphiel, CM.\", \"from\": 976, \"to\": 1232, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1130, \"end\": 1147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raymond_Leo_Burke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Raymond Leo Burke\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raymond_Leo_Burke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raymond_Leo_Burke\"}, {\"begin\": 1138, \"end\": 1147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Burke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.21922638379628e-15, \"text\": \"Leo Burke\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Burke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Burke\"}, {\"begin\": 1178, \"end\": 1181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franciscans\", \"score\": 0.9999999977467269, \"rank\": 1.9518581408646435e-09, \"text\": \"OFM\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franciscans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franciscans\"}, {\"begin\": 1196, \"end\": 1227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berhaneyesus_Demerew_Souraphiel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Berhaneyesus Demerew Souraphiel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berhaneyesus_Demerew_Souraphiel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berhaneyesus_Demerew_Souraphiel\"}, {\"begin\": 1229, \"end\": 1232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Command_paper\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"CM.\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Command_paper\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Command_paper\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the faith\", \"from\": 1006, \"to\": 1015}, {\"ngram\": \"over 2 billion people\", \"from\": 1019, \"to\": 1040}, {\"ngram\": \"the prelates\", \"from\": 1095, \"to\": 1107}, {\"ngram\": \"Cardinal Wilfrid Fox Napier\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1176}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While 15 of the24 signatoriesare from the U.S. - including Archbishop Samuel Aquila of Denver; Archbishop Emeritus Charles Chaput of Philadelphia; Archbishop Salvatore Cordileone of San Francisco; Archbishop James Conley of Lincoln, Nebraska; and Archbishop Andrew Cozzens of Crookston, Minnesota - bishops from Argentina, France, Ghana, Lebanon, Nigeria, Peru, and the United Kingdom also signed the letter.\", \"from\": 1234, \"to\": 1642, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1293, \"end\": 1303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"score\": 0.9999818410344988, \"rank\": 1.763960065411712e-05, \"text\": \"Archbishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\"}, {\"begin\": 1304, \"end\": 1317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_J._Aquila\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Samuel Aquila\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_J._Aquila\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_J._Aquila\"}, {\"begin\": 1321, \"end\": 1327, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denver\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.662247395059099e-16, \"text\": \"Denver\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denver\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denver\"}, {\"begin\": 1329, \"end\": 1348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"score\": 0.9999831156285175, \"rank\": 1.6884656369316913e-05, \"text\": \"Archbishop Emeritus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\"}, {\"begin\": 1349, \"end\": 1363, \"title\":